column1: #Text=# DartMinHash: Fast Sketching for Weighted Sets
#Text=This repository contains experiments for comparing the estimation accuracy and running times of the following weighted minwise hashing algorithms:
#Text=For BagMinHash and ICWS we use the implementation from here https://github.com/oertl/bagminhash with the relevant files included in the /bagminhash folder.
#Text=See the DartMinHash paper https://arxiv.org/abs/2005.11547 for a description of the algorithm and further results of experiments.
#Text=The BagMinHash algorithm uses XXHash64 which must be installed:
#Text=Get xxhash from https://github.com/Cyan4973/xxHash, e.g. using `git clone https://github.com/Cyan4973/xxHash.git`
#Text=Place xxhash.h and libxxhash.a into the directory /bagminhash/xxhash
#Text=The code compiles under GCC version 7.5.0 https://gcc.gnu.org/ with relevant commands in the makefile https://www.gnu.org/software/make/.
#Text=`make run` compiles and executes the main function in main.cpp.
#Text=`make test` compiles and run unit tests.
#Text=The different experiments are all placed in the main.cpp and write their output to stdout in CSV format.
#Text=`time_performance`: Times different algorithms on synthetic data for all combinations of sketch lengths, and L0 and L1 norms chosen.
#Text=`time_performance_specific`: Same as above, but only runs on specified tuples of parameters.
#Text=`measure_similarity`: Returns the estimated Jaccard similarity of different algorithms on synthetic pairs of weighted sets with a specific similarity.
#Text=By default `make run` will run `time_performance_specific` on a subset of the settings used in Table 1 in the paper.
#Text=In order to pipe the output to the file `data.csv` use command `make run > data.csv`.
#Text=* t denotes the sketch length (usually k in the paper).
#Text=* ICWS is a simple and unoptimized version of ICWS using tabulation hashing.
#Text=* ICWS_xxhash is the implementation from the BagMinHash repository which uses the ziggurat algorithm for fast sampling: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ziggurat_algorithm
#Text=* FastICWS is our own highly optimized implementation of ICWS that tabulates expensive operations and only computes the logarithms of weights once.
#Text=* BagMinHash1 and BagMinHash2: BagMinHash variants described in the BagMinHash paper.
#Text=BagMinHash2 is essentially always faster and is what we compare against.
#Text=* DartMinHash: Optimized implementation following the pseudocode in the paper.
#Text=| id | L0   | log2_L1 | t    | ICWS    | FastICWS | ICWS_xxhash | BagMinHash1 | BagMinHash2 | DartMinHash |
#Text=| sim_j | t  | ICWS_xxhash | FastICWS | BagMinHash2 | DartMinHash |
#Text=We use Catch2 https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2 for unit testing.
#Text=To compile and run tests use the command: `make test`
